
<item rdf:about='http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-bosch-sieve-special-use-02.txt'>
    <title>"Sieve Email Filtering: Delivering to Special-Use Mailboxes", Stephan Bosch</title>
    <link>http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-bosch-sieve-special-use-02.txt</link>
    <description>The SPECIAL-USE capability of the IMAP protocol (RFC 6154) allows clients to identify special-use mailboxes; e.g., where draft or sent messages should be put.  This simplifies client configuration.  In contrast, the Sieve mail filtering language (RFC 5228) currently has no such capability.  This memo defines a Sieve extension that fills this gap: it adds a test for checking whether a special-use attribute is assigned for a particular mailbox or any mailbox, and it adds the ability to file messages into an anonymous mailbox that has a particular special-use attribute assigned.</description>
    <dc:date>2017-04-21T07:00:00-00:00</dc:date>
</item>
